44VendorID GetVendorID(const FunctionsGL *functions)
45{
46 std::string nativeVendorString(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(functions->getString(GL_VENDOR)));
47 // Concatenate GL_RENDERER to the string being checked because some vendors put their names in
48 // GL_RENDERER
49 nativeVendorString +=
50 " " + std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(functions->getString(GL_RENDERER)));
51 if (nativeVendorString.find("NVIDIA") != std::string::npos)
52 {
53 return VENDOR_ID_NVIDIA;
54 }
55 else if (nativeVendorString.find("ATI") != std::string::npos ||
56 nativeVendorString.find("AMD") != std::string::npos ||
57 nativeVendorString.find("Radeon") != std::string::npos)
58 {
59 return VENDOR_ID_AMD;
60 }
61 else if (nativeVendorString.find("Qualcomm") != std::string::npos)
62 {
63 return VENDOR_ID_QUALCOMM;
64 }
65 else if (nativeVendorString.find("Intel") != std::string::npos)
66 {
67 return VENDOR_ID_INTEL;
68 }
69 else
70 {
71 return VENDOR_ID_UNKNOWN;
72 }
73}
74
75uint32_t GetDeviceID(const FunctionsGL *functions)
76{
77 std::string nativeRendererString(
78 reinterpret_cast<const char *>(functions->getString(GL_RENDERER)));
79 constexpr std::pair<const char *, uint32_t> kKnownDeviceIDs[] = {
80 {"Adreno (TM) 418", ANDROID_DEVICE_ID_NEXUS5X},
81 {"Adreno (TM) 530", ANDROID_DEVICE_ID_PIXEL1XL},
82 {"Adreno (TM) 540", ANDROID_DEVICE_ID_PIXEL2},
83 };
84
85 for (const auto &knownDeviceID : kKnownDeviceIDs)
86 {
87 if (nativeRendererString.find(knownDeviceID.first) != std::string::npos)
88 {
89 return knownDeviceID.second;
90 }
91 }
92
93 return 0;
94}

96bool IsMesa(const FunctionsGL *functions, std::array<int, 3> *version)
97{
98 ASSERT(version);
99
100 if (functions->standard != STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP)
101 {
102 return false;
103 }
104
105 std::string nativeVersionString(
106 reinterpret_cast<const char *>(functions->getString(GL_VERSION)));
107 size_t pos = nativeVersionString.find("Mesa");
108 if (pos == std::string::npos)
109 {
110 return false;
111 }
112
113 int *data = version->data();
114 data[0] = data[1] = data[2] = 0;
115 std::sscanf(nativeVersionString.c_str() + pos, "Mesa %d.%d.%d", data, data + 1, data + 2);
116
117 return true;
118}

123static bool MeetsRequirements(const FunctionsGL *functions,
124 const nativegl::SupportRequirement &requirements)
125{
126 bool hasRequiredExtensions = false;
127 for (const std::vector<std::string> &exts : requirements.requiredExtensions)
128 {
129 bool hasAllExtensionsInSet = true;
130 for (const std::string &extension : exts)
131 {
132 if (!functions->hasExtension(extension))
133 {
134 hasAllExtensionsInSet = false;
135 break;
136 }
137 }
138 if (hasAllExtensionsInSet)
139 {
140 hasRequiredExtensions = true;
141 break;
142 }
143 }
144 if (!requirements.requiredExtensions.empty() && !hasRequiredExtensions)
145 {
146 return false;
147 }
148
149 if (functions->version >= requirements.version)
150 {
151 return true;
152 }
153 else if (!requirements.versionExtensions.empty())
154 {
155 for (const std::string &extension : requirements.versionExtensions)
156 {
157 if (!functions->hasExtension(extension))
158 {
159 return false;
160 }
161 }
162 return true;
163 }
164 else
165 {
166 return false;
167 }
168}

170static bool CheckSizedInternalFormatTextureRenderability(const FunctionsGL *functions,
171 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
172 GLenum internalFormat)
173{
174 const gl::InternalFormat &formatInfo = gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
175 ASSERT(formatInfo.sized);
176
177 // Query the current texture so it can be rebound afterwards
178 GLint oldTextureBinding = 0;
179 functions->getIntegerv(GL_TEXTURE_BINDING_2D, &oldTextureBinding);
180
181 // Create a small texture with the same format and type that gl::Texture would use
182 GLuint texture = 0;
183 functions->genTextures(1, &texture);
184 functions->bindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, texture);
185
186 // Nearest filter needed for framebuffer completeness on some drivers.
187 functions->texParameteri(GL_TEXTURE_2D, GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, GL_NEAREST);
188
189 nativegl::TexImageFormat texImageFormat = nativegl::GetTexImageFormat(
190 functions, features, formatInfo.internalFormat, formatInfo.format, formatInfo.type);
191 constexpr GLsizei kTextureSize = 16;
192 functions->texImage2D(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, texImageFormat.internalFormat, kTextureSize,
193 kTextureSize, 0, texImageFormat.format, texImageFormat.type, nullptr);
194
195 // Query the current framebuffer so it can be rebound afterwards
196 GLint oldFramebufferBinding = 0;
197 functions->getIntegerv(GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, &oldFramebufferBinding);
198
199 // Bind the texture to the framebuffer and check renderability
200 GLuint fbo = 0;
201 functions->genFramebuffers(1, &fbo);
202 functions->bindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, fbo);
203 functions->framebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, GL_TEXTURE_2D, texture,
204 0);
205
206 bool supported = functions->checkFramebufferStatus(GL_FRAMEBUFFER) == GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE;
207
208 // Delete the framebuffer and restore the previous binding
209 functions->deleteFramebuffers(1, &fbo);
210 functions->bindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, static_cast<GLuint>(oldFramebufferBinding));
211
212 // Delete the texture and restore the previous binding
213 functions->deleteTextures(1, &texture);
214 functions->bindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, static_cast<GLuint>(oldTextureBinding));
215
216 return supported;
217}
218
219static bool CheckInternalFormatRenderbufferRenderability(const FunctionsGL *functions,
220 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
221 GLenum internalFormat)
222{
223 const gl::InternalFormat &formatInfo = gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
224 ASSERT(formatInfo.sized);
225
226 // Query the current renderbuffer so it can be rebound afterwards
227 GLint oldRenderbufferBinding = 0;
228 functions->getIntegerv(GL_RENDERBUFFER_BINDING, &oldRenderbufferBinding);
229
230 // Create a small renderbuffer with the same format and type that gl::Renderbuffer would use
231 GLuint renderbuffer = 0;
232 functions->genRenderbuffers(1, &renderbuffer);
233 functions->bindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbuffer);
234
235 nativegl::RenderbufferFormat renderbufferFormat =
236 nativegl::GetRenderbufferFormat(functions, features, formatInfo.internalFormat);
237 constexpr GLsizei kRenderbufferSize = 16;
238 functions->renderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbufferFormat.internalFormat,
239 kRenderbufferSize, kRenderbufferSize);
240
241 // Query the current framebuffer so it can be rebound afterwards
242 GLint oldFramebufferBinding = 0;
243 functions->getIntegerv(GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, &oldFramebufferBinding);
244
245 // Bind the texture to the framebuffer and check renderability
246 GLuint fbo = 0;
247 functions->genFramebuffers(1, &fbo);
248 functions->bindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, fbo);
249 functions->framebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, GL_RENDERBUFFER,
250 renderbuffer);
251
252 bool supported = functions->checkFramebufferStatus(GL_FRAMEBUFFER) == GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE;
253
254 // Delete the framebuffer and restore the previous binding
255 functions->deleteFramebuffers(1, &fbo);
256 functions->bindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, static_cast<GLuint>(oldFramebufferBinding));
257
258 // Delete the renderbuffer and restore the previous binding
259 functions->deleteRenderbuffers(1, &renderbuffer);
260 functions->bindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, static_cast<GLuint>(oldRenderbufferBinding));
261
262 return supported;
263}
264
265static void LimitVersion(gl::Version *curVersion, const gl::Version &maxVersion)
266{
267 if (*curVersion >= maxVersion)
268 {
269 *curVersion = maxVersion;
270 }
271}

273static gl::TextureCaps GenerateTextureFormatCaps(const FunctionsGL *functions,
274 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
275 GLenum internalFormat,
276 gl::Version *maxSupportedESVersion)
277{
278 ASSERT(functions->getError() == GL_NO_ERROR);
279
280 gl::TextureCaps textureCaps;
281
282 const nativegl::InternalFormat &formatInfo =
283 nativegl::GetInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat, functions->standard);
284 textureCaps.texturable = MeetsRequirements(functions, formatInfo.texture);
285 textureCaps.filterable =
286 textureCaps.texturable && MeetsRequirements(functions, formatInfo.filter);
287 textureCaps.textureAttachment = MeetsRequirements(functions, formatInfo.textureAttachment);
288 textureCaps.renderbuffer = MeetsRequirements(functions, formatInfo.renderbuffer);
289 textureCaps.blendable = textureCaps.renderbuffer || textureCaps.textureAttachment;
290
291 // Do extra renderability validation for some formats.
292 if (internalFormat == GL_R16F || internalFormat == GL_RG16F || internalFormat == GL_RGB16F)
293 {
294 // SupportRequirement can't currently express a condition of the form (version && extension)
295 // || other extensions, so do the (version && extension) part here.
296 if (functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)) &&
297 functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_EXT_color_buffer_half_float"))
298 {
299 textureCaps.textureAttachment = true;
300 textureCaps.renderbuffer = true;
301 }
302 }
303
304 // We require GL_RGBA16F is renderable to expose EXT_color_buffer_half_float but we can't know
305 // if the format is supported unless we try to create a framebuffer.
306 if (internalFormat == GL_RGBA16F)
307 {
308 if (textureCaps.textureAttachment)
309 {
310 textureCaps.textureAttachment =
311 CheckSizedInternalFormatTextureRenderability(functions, features, internalFormat);
312 }
313 if (textureCaps.renderbuffer)
314 {
315 textureCaps.renderbuffer =
316 CheckInternalFormatRenderbufferRenderability(functions, features, internalFormat);
317 }
318 }
319
320 // glGetInternalformativ is not available until version 4.2 but may be available through the 3.0
321 // extension GL_ARB_internalformat_query
322 if (textureCaps.renderbuffer && functions->getInternalformativ)
323 {
324 GLenum queryInternalFormat = internalFormat;
325
326 if (internalFormat == GL_BGRA8_EXT)
327 {
328 // Querying GL_NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS for GL_BGRA8_EXT generates an INVALID_ENUM on some
329 // drivers. It seems however that allocating a multisampled renderbuffer of this format
330 // succeeds. To avoid breaking multisampling for this format, query the supported sample
331 // counts for GL_RGBA8 instead.
332 queryInternalFormat = GL_RGBA8;
333 }
334
335 GLint numSamples = 0;
336 functions->getInternalformativ(GL_RENDERBUFFER, queryInternalFormat, GL_NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS,
337 1, &numSamples);
338
339 if (numSamples > 0)
340 {
341 std::vector<GLint> samples(numSamples);
342 functions->getInternalformativ(GL_RENDERBUFFER, queryInternalFormat, GL_SAMPLES,
343 static_cast<GLsizei>(samples.size()), &samples[0]);
344
345 if (internalFormat == GL_STENCIL_INDEX8)
346 {
347 // The query below does generates an error with STENCIL_INDEX8 on NVIDIA driver
348 // 382.33. So for now we assume that the same sampling modes are conformant for
349 // STENCIL_INDEX8 as for DEPTH24_STENCIL8. Clean this up once the driver is fixed.
350 // http://anglebug.com/2059
351 queryInternalFormat = GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8;
352 }
353 for (size_t sampleIndex = 0; sampleIndex < samples.size(); sampleIndex++)
354 {
355 if (features.limitMaxMSAASamplesTo4.enabled && samples[sampleIndex] > 4)
356 {
357 continue;
358 }
359
360 // Some NVIDIA drivers expose multisampling modes implemented as a combination of
361 // multisampling and supersampling. These are non-conformant and should not be
362 // exposed through ANGLE. Query which formats are conformant from the driver if
363 // supported.
364 GLint conformant = GL_TRUE;
365 if (functions->getInternalformatSampleivNV)
366 {
367 ASSERT(functions->getError() == GL_NO_ERROR);
368 functions->getInternalformatSampleivNV(GL_RENDERBUFFER, queryInternalFormat,
369 samples[sampleIndex], GL_CONFORMANT_NV,
370 1, &conformant);
371 // getInternalFormatSampleivNV does not work for all formats on NVIDIA Shield TV
372 // drivers. Assume that formats with large sample counts are non-conformant in
373 // case the query generates an error.
374 if (functions->getError() != GL_NO_ERROR)
375 {
376 conformant = (samples[sampleIndex] <= 8) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
377 }
378 }
379 if (conformant == GL_TRUE)
380 {
381 textureCaps.sampleCounts.insert(samples[sampleIndex]);
382 }
383 }
384 }
385 }
386
387 // GLES 3.0.5 section 4.4.2.2: "Implementations must support creation of renderbuffers in these
388 // required formats with up to the value of MAX_SAMPLES multisamples, with the exception of
389 // signed and unsigned integer formats."
390 const gl::InternalFormat &glFormatInfo = gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
391 if (textureCaps.renderbuffer && !glFormatInfo.isInt() &&
392 glFormatInfo.isRequiredRenderbufferFormat(gl::Version(3, 0)) &&
393 textureCaps.getMaxSamples() < 4)
394 {
395 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(2, 0));
396 }
397
398 ASSERT(functions->getError() == GL_NO_ERROR);
399 return textureCaps;
400}

423static GLint64 QuerySingleGLInt64(const FunctionsGL *functions, GLenum name)
424{
425 // Fall back to 32-bit int if 64-bit query is not available. This can become relevant for some
426 // caps that are defined as 64-bit values in core spec, but were introduced earlier in
427 // extensions as 32-bit. Triggered in some cases by RenderDoc's emulated OpenGL driver.
428 if (!functions->getInteger64v)
429 {
430 GLint result = 0;
431 functions->getIntegerv(name, &result);
432 return static_cast<GLint64>(result);
433 }
434 else
435 {
436 GLint64 result = 0;
437 functions->getInteger64v(name, &result);
438 return result;
439 }
440}

442static GLfloat QuerySingleGLFloat(const FunctionsGL *functions, GLenum name)
443{
444 GLfloat result = 0.0f;
445 functions->getFloatv(name, &result);
446 return result;

473void CapCombinedLimitToESShaders(GLint *combinedLimit, gl::ShaderMap<GLint> &perShaderLimit)
474{
475 GLint combinedESLimit = 0;
476 for (gl::ShaderType shaderType : gl::kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
477 {
478 combinedESLimit += perShaderLimit[shaderType];
479 }
480
481 *combinedLimit = std::min(*combinedLimit, combinedESLimit);
482}

484void GenerateCaps(const FunctionsGL *functions,
485 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
486 gl::Caps *caps,
487 gl::TextureCapsMap *textureCapsMap,
488 gl::Extensions *extensions,
489 gl::Version *maxSupportedESVersion,
490 MultiviewImplementationTypeGL *multiviewImplementationType)
491{
492 // Start by assuming ES3.1 support and work down
493 *maxSupportedESVersion = gl::Version(3, 1);
494
495 // Texture format support checks
496 const gl::FormatSet &allFormats = gl::GetAllSizedInternalFormats();
497 for (GLenum internalFormat : allFormats)
498 {
499 gl::TextureCaps textureCaps =
500 GenerateTextureFormatCaps(functions, features, internalFormat, maxSupportedESVersion);
501 textureCapsMap->insert(internalFormat, textureCaps);
502
503 if (gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat).compressed)
504 {
505 caps->compressedTextureFormats.push_back(internalFormat);
506 }
507 }
508
509 // Table 6.28, implementation dependent values
510 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 3)) ||
511 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_ES3_compatibility") ||
512 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
513 {
514 caps->maxElementIndex = QuerySingleGLInt64(functions, GL_MAX_ELEMENT_INDEX);
515
516 // Work around the null driver limitations.
517 if (caps->maxElementIndex == 0)
518 {
519 caps->maxElementIndex = 0xFFFF;
520 }
521 }
522 else
523 {
524 // Doesn't affect ES3 support, can use a pre-defined limit
525 caps->maxElementIndex = static_cast<GLint64>(std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max());
526 }
527
528 GLint textureSizeLimit = std::numeric_limits<GLint>::max();
529 if (features.limitMaxTextureSizeTo4096.enabled)
530 {
531 textureSizeLimit = 4096;
532 }
533
534 GLint max3dArrayTextureSizeLimit = std::numeric_limits<GLint>::max();
535 if (features.limitMax3dArrayTextureSizeTo1024.enabled)
536 {
537 max3dArrayTextureSizeLimit = 1024;
538 }
539
540 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(1, 2)) || functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)) ||
541 functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_3D"))
542 {
543 caps->max3DTextureSize = std::min({QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_3D_TEXTURE_SIZE),
544 textureSizeLimit, max3dArrayTextureSizeLimit});
545 }
546 else
547 {
548 // Can't support ES3 without 3D textures
549 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(2, 0));
550 }
551
552 caps->max2DTextureSize = std::min(QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE),
553 textureSizeLimit); // GL 1.0 / ES 2.0
554 caps->maxCubeMapTextureSize =
555 std::min(QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_CUBE_MAP_TEXTURE_SIZE),
556 textureSizeLimit); // GL 1.3 / ES 2.0
557
558 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(3, 0)) ||
559 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_EXT_texture_array") ||
560 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
561 {
562 caps->maxArrayTextureLayers =
563 std::min({QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_ARRAY_TEXTURE_LAYERS), textureSizeLimit,
564 max3dArrayTextureSizeLimit});
565 }
566 else
567 {
568 // Can't support ES3 without array textures
569 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(2, 0));
570 }
571
572 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(1, 5)) ||
573 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_EXT_texture_lod_bias") ||
574 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
575 {
576 caps->maxLODBias = QuerySingleGLFloat(functions, GL_MAX_TEXTURE_LOD_BIAS);
577 }
578 else
579 {
580 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(2, 0));
581 }
582
583 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(3, 0)) ||
584 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_EXT_framebuffer_object") ||
585 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(2, 0)))
586 {
587 caps->maxRenderbufferSize = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_RENDERBUFFER_SIZE);
588 caps->maxColorAttachments = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS);
589 }
590 else
591 {
592 // Can't support ES2 without framebuffers and renderbuffers
593 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(0, 0));
594 }
595
596 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(2, 0)) ||
597 functions->hasGLExtension("ARB_draw_buffers") ||
598 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)) ||
599 functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_EXT_draw_buffers"))
600 {
601 caps->maxDrawBuffers = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS);
602 }
603 else
604 {
605 // Framebuffer is required to have at least one drawbuffer even if the extension is not
606 // supported
607 caps->maxDrawBuffers = 1;
608 LimitVersion(maxSupportedESVersion, gl::Version(2, 0));
609 }
610
611 caps->maxViewportWidth =
612 QueryGLIntRange(functions, GL_MAX_VIEWPORT_DIMS, 0); // GL 1.0 / ES 2.0
613 caps->maxViewportHeight =
614 QueryGLIntRange(functions, GL_MAX_VIEWPORT_DIMS, 1); // GL 1.0 / ES 2.0
615
616 if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP &&
617 (functions->profile & GL_CONTEXT_CORE_PROFILE_BIT) != 0)
618 {
619 // Desktop GL core profile deprecated the GL_ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE query. Use
620 // GL_POINT_SIZE_RANGE instead.
621 caps->minAliasedPointSize =
622 std::max(1.0f, QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_POINT_SIZE_RANGE, 0));
623 caps->maxAliasedPointSize = QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_POINT_SIZE_RANGE, 1);
624 }
625 else
626 {
627 caps->minAliasedPointSize =
628 std::max(1.0f, QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE, 0));
629 caps->maxAliasedPointSize = QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE, 1);
630 }
631
632 caps->minAliasedLineWidth =
633 QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE, 0); // GL 1.2 / ES 2.0
634 caps->maxAliasedLineWidth =
635 QueryGLFloatRange(functions, GL_ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE, 1); // GL 1.2 / ES 2.0
636
637 // Table 6.29, implementation dependent values (cont.)
638 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(1, 2)) || functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
639 {
640 caps->maxElementsIndices = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_ELEMENTS_INDICES);
641 caps->maxElementsVertices = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_MAX_ELEMENTS_VERTICES);
642 }
643 else
644 {
645 // Doesn't impact supported version
646 }
647
648 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 1)) ||
649 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_get_program_binary") ||
650 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)) ||
651 functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_get_program_binary"))
652 {
653 // Able to support the GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE format as long as another program binary
654 // format is available.
655 GLint numBinaryFormats = QuerySingleGLInt(functions, GL_NUM_PROGRAM_BINARY_FORMATS_OES);
656 if (numBinaryFormats > 0)
657 {
658 caps->programBinaryFormats.push_back(GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE);
659 }
660 }
661 else
662 {
663 // Doesn't impact supported version
664 }
665
666 // glGetShaderPrecisionFormat is not available until desktop GL version 4.1 or
667 // GL_ARB_ES2_compatibility exists
668 if (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 1)) ||
669 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_ES2_compatibility") ||
670 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(2, 0)))
671 {
672 caps->vertexHighpFloat = QueryTypePrecision(functions, GL_VERTEX_SHADER, GL_HIGH_FLOAT);
673 caps->vertexMediumpFloat = QueryTypePrecision(functions, GL_VERTEX_SHADER, GL_MEDIUM_FLOAT);

1591
1592void InitializeFeatures(const FunctionsGL *functions, angle::FeaturesGL *features)
1593{
1594 angle::VendorID vendor;
1595 angle::DeviceID device;
1596
1597 angle::SystemInfo systemInfo;
1598 bool isGetSystemInfoSuccess = angle::GetSystemInfo(&systemInfo);
1599 if (isGetSystemInfoSuccess)
1600 {
1601 vendor = systemInfo.gpus[systemInfo.activeGPUIndex].vendorId;
1602 device = systemInfo.gpus[systemInfo.activeGPUIndex].deviceId;
1603 }
1604 else
1605 {
1606 vendor = GetVendorID(functions);
1607 device = GetDeviceID(functions);
1608 }
1609
1610 bool isAMD = IsAMD(vendor);
1611 bool isIntel = IsIntel(vendor);
1612 bool isNvidia = IsNvidia(vendor);
1613 bool isQualcomm = IsQualcomm(vendor);
1614 bool isVMWare = IsVMWare(vendor);
1615 bool hasAMD = systemInfo.hasAMDGPU();
1616
1617 std::array<int, 3> mesaVersion = {0, 0, 0};
1618 bool isMesa = IsMesa(functions, &mesaVersion);
1619
1620 // Don't use 1-bit alpha formats on desktop GL with AMD drivers.
1621 ANGLE_FEATURE_CONDITION(features, avoid1BitAlphaTextureFormats,

1885bool SupportsCompute(const FunctionsGL *functions)
1886{
1887 // OpenGL 4.2 is required for GL_ARB_compute_shader, some platform drivers have the extension,
1888 // but their maximum supported GL versions are less than 4.2. Explicitly limit the minimum
1889 // GL version to 4.2.
1890 return (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 3)) ||
1891 functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 1)) ||
1892 (functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 2)) &&
1893 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_compute_shader") &&
1894 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_shader_storage_buffer_object")));
1895}

1910
1911bool SupportsNativeRendering(const FunctionsGL *functions,
1912 gl::TextureType type,
1913 GLenum internalFormat)
1914{
1915 // Some desktop drivers allow rendering to formats that are not required by the spec, this is
1916 // exposed through the GL_FRAMEBUFFER_RENDERABLE query.
1917 bool hasInternalFormatQuery = functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 3)) ||
1918 functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_internalformat_query2");
1919
1920 // Some Intel drivers have a bug that returns GL_FULL_SUPPORT when asked if they support
1921 // rendering to compressed texture formats yet return framebuffer incomplete when attempting to
1922 // render to the format. Skip any native queries for compressed formats.
1923 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormatInfo = gl::GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat);
1924
1925 if (hasInternalFormatQuery && !internalFormatInfo.compressed)
1926 {
1927 GLint framebufferRenderable = GL_NONE;
1928 functions->getInternalformativ(ToGLenum(type), internalFormat, GL_FRAMEBUFFER_RENDERABLE, 1,
1929 &framebufferRenderable);
1930 return framebufferRenderable != GL_NONE;
1931 }
1932 else
1933 {
1934 const nativegl::InternalFormat &nativeInfo =
1935 nativegl::GetInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat, functions->standard);
1936 return nativegl_gl::MeetsRequirements(functions, nativeInfo.textureAttachment);
1937 }
1938}

2050gl::TextureType GetNativeTextureType(gl::TextureType type)
2051{
2052 // VideoImage texture type is a WebGL type. It doesn't have
2053 // directly mapping type in native OpenGL/OpenGLES.
2054 // Actually, it will be translated to different texture type
2055 // (TEXTURE2D, TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES and TEXTURE_RECTANGLE)
2056 // based on OS and other conditions.
2057 // This will introduce problem that binding VideoImage may
2058 // unbind native image implicitly. Please make sure state
2059 // manager is aware of this implicit unbind behaviour.
2060 if (type != gl::TextureType::VideoImage)
2061 {
2062 return type;
2063 }
2064
2065 // TODO(http://anglebug.com/3889): need to figure out rectangle texture and
2066 // external image when these backend are implemented.
2067 return gl::TextureType::_2D;
2068}

2116
2117void ClearErrors(const gl::Context *context,
2118 const char *file,
2119 const char *function,
2120 unsigned int line)
2121{
2122 const FunctionsGL *functions = GetFunctionsGL(context);
2123
2124 GLenum error = functions->getError();
2125 while (error != GL_NO_ERROR)
2126 {
2127 ERR() << "Preexisting GL error " << gl::FmtHex(error) << " as of " << file << ", "
2128 << function << ":" << line << ". ";
2129 error = functions->getError();
2130 }
2131}
2132
2133angle::Result CheckError(const gl::Context *context,
2134 const char *call,
2135 const char *file,
2136 const char *function,
2137 unsigned int line)
2138{
2139 const FunctionsGL *functions = GetFunctionsGL(context);
2140
2141 GLenum error = functions->getError();
2142 if (ANGLE_UNLIKELY(error != GL_NO_ERROR))
2143 {
2144 ContextGL *contextGL = GetImplAs<ContextGL>(context);
2145 contextGL->handleError(error, "Unexpected driver error.", file, function, line);
2146 ERR() << "GL call " << call << " generated error " << gl::FmtHex(error) << " in " << file
2147 << ", " << function << ":" << line << ". ";
2148
2149 // Check that only one GL error was generated, ClearErrors should have been called first.
2150 // Skip GL_CONTEXT_LOST errors, they will be generated continuously and result in an
2151 // infinite loop.
2152 GLenum nextError = functions->getError();
2153 while (nextError != GL_NO_ERROR && nextError != GL_CONTEXT_LOST)
2154 {
2155 ERR() << "Additional GL error " << gl::FmtHex(nextError) << " generated.";
2156 nextError = functions->getError();
2157 }
2158
2159 return angle::Result::Stop;
2160 }
2161
2162 return angle::Result::Continue;
2163}

2170
2171uint8_t *MapBufferRangeWithFallback(const FunctionsGL *functions,
2172 GLenum target,
2173 size_t offset,
2174 size_t length,
2175 GLbitfield access)
2176{
2177 if (functions->mapBufferRange != nullptr)
2178 {
2179 return static_cast<uint8_t *>(functions->mapBufferRange(target, offset, length, access));
2180 }
2181 else if (functions->mapBuffer != nullptr &&
2182 (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP || access == GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT))
2183 {
2184 // Only the read and write bits are supported
2185 ASSERT((access & (GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT)) != 0);
2186
2187 GLenum accessEnum = 0;
2188 if (access == (GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT))
2189 {
2190 accessEnum = GL_READ_WRITE;
2191 }
2192 else if (access == GL_MAP_READ_BIT)
2193 {
2194 accessEnum = GL_READ_ONLY;
2195 }
2196 else if (access == GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT)
2197 {
2198 accessEnum = GL_WRITE_ONLY;
2199 }
2200 else
2201 {
2202 UNREACHABLE();
2203 return nullptr;
2204 }
2205
2206 return static_cast<uint8_t *>(functions->mapBuffer(target, accessEnum)) + offset;
2207 }
2208 else
2209 {
2210 // No options available
2211 UNREACHABLE();
2212 return nullptr;
2213 }
2214}
2215
2216angle::Result ShouldApplyLastRowPaddingWorkaround(ContextGL *contextGL,
2217 const gl::Extents &size,
2218 const gl::PixelStoreStateBase &state,
2219 const gl::Buffer *pixelBuffer,
2220 GLenum format,
2221 GLenum type,
2222 bool is3D,
2223 const void *pixels,
2224 bool *shouldApplyOut)
2225{
2226 if (pixelBuffer == nullptr)
2227 {
2228 *shouldApplyOut = false;
2229 return angle::Result::Continue;
2230 }
2231
2232 // We are using an pack or unpack buffer, compute what the driver thinks is going to be the
2233 // last byte read or written. If it is past the end of the buffer, we will need to use the
2234 // workaround otherwise the driver will generate INVALID_OPERATION and not do the operation.
2235
2236 const gl::InternalFormat &glFormat = gl::GetInternalFormatInfo(format, type);
2237 GLuint endByte = 0;
2238 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextGL,
2239 glFormat.computePackUnpackEndByte(type, size, state, is3D, &endByte));
2240 GLuint rowPitch = 0;
2241 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextGL, glFormat.computeRowPitch(type, size.width, state.alignment,
2242 state.rowLength, &rowPitch));
2243
2244 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedPixelBytes = glFormat.computePixelBytes(type);
2245 CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedEndByte =
2246 angle::CheckedNumeric<size_t>(endByte) + reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(pixels);
2247
2248 // At this point checkedEndByte is the actual last byte read.
2249 // The driver adds an extra row padding (if any), mimic it.
2250 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextGL, checkedPixelBytes.IsValid());
2251 if (checkedPixelBytes.ValueOrDie() * size.width < rowPitch)
2252 {
2253 checkedEndByte += rowPitch - checkedPixelBytes * size.width;
2254 }
2255
2256 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_MATH(contextGL, checkedEndByte.IsValid());
2257
2258 *shouldApplyOut = checkedEndByte.ValueOrDie() > static_cast<size_t>(pixelBuffer->getSize());
2259 return angle::Result::Continue;
2260}

2262std::vector<ContextCreationTry> GenerateContextCreationToTry(EGLint requestedType, bool isMesaGLX)
2263{
2264 using Type = ContextCreationTry::Type;
2265 constexpr EGLint kPlatformOpenGL = EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGL_ANGLE;
2266 constexpr EGLint kPlatformOpenGLES = EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGLES_ANGLE;
2267
2268 std::vector<ContextCreationTry> contextsToTry;
2269
2270 if (requestedType == EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_DEFAULT_ANGLE || requestedType == kPlatformOpenGL)
2271 {
2272 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 5));
2273 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 4));
2274 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 3));
2275 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 2));
2276 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 1));
2277 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(4, 0));
2278 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(3, 3));
2279 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_CORE, gl::Version(3, 2));
2280 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(3, 3));
2281
2282 // On Mesa, do not try to create OpenGL context versions between 3.0 and
2283 // 3.2 because of compatibility problems. See crbug.com/659030
2284 if (!isMesaGLX)
2285 {
2286 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(3, 2));
2287 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(3, 1));
2288 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(3, 0));
2289 }
2290
2291 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(2, 1));
2292 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(2, 0));
2293 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 5));
2294 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 4));
2295 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 3));
2296 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 2));
2297 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 1));
2298 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGL, Type::DESKTOP_LEGACY, gl::Version(1, 0));
2299 }
2300
2301 if (requestedType == EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_DEFAULT_ANGLE ||
2302 requestedType == kPlatformOpenGLES)
2303 {
2304 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGLES, Type::ES, gl::Version(3, 2));
2305 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGLES, Type::ES, gl::Version(3, 1));
2306 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGLES, Type::ES, gl::Version(3, 0));
2307 contextsToTry.emplace_back(kPlatformOpenGLES, Type::ES, gl::Version(2, 0));
2308 }
2309
2310 return contextsToTry;
2311}
